-- MOVES-China Renaissance Securities names Gloria Lu as head of equities
-- 
-- Mon Aug 18, 2014 10:02PM EDT
-- None



HONG KONG, Aug 19 (Reuters) - China Renaissance Securities has hired Gloria Lu as its new head of equities based in Hong Kong, the China-based boutique investment bank said in an internal memo seen by Reuters on Tuesday.

Lu previously worked at China Life Franklin Asset Management as deputy chief executive, the memo said. Her appointment is the second senior hire by China Renaissance in the last month, after it appointed former JPMorgan executive Yang Diao as co-head of investment banking on July 21. [ID:nL4N0PW109] A spokesman for China Renaissance confirmed the contents of the memo.